{{Transcript|Quest}}
{{Transcript list|Clay golem|Elissa|Curator Haig Halen}}

==Talking to the golem to start the quest==
* '''Broken clay golem:''' Damage... severe... Task... incomplete...
* {{tselect|Start The Golem quest?}}
* {{topt|Yes}}
** '''Player:''' Shall I try to repair you?
** '''Broken clay golem:''' Repairs... needed...
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No}}
** '''Player:''' I'm not going to find a conversation here!
** '''Broken clay golem:''' Graar!
** '''Broken clay golem:''' Must... not... injure... human...
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Golem after starting the quest===
* '''Broken clay golem:''' Damage... severe...
* {{tact|end}}

==Using the soft clay on the golem==
===Before starting the quest===
* {{mes|Maybe you should ask the golem first!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After using the first soft clay===
* {{tbox|pic=Soft clay detail.png|You apply some clay to the golem's wounds. The clay begins to harden in the hot sun.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After using the second soft clay===
* {{tbox|pic=Soft clay detail.png|You fix the golem's legs.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After using the third soft clay===
* {{tbox|pic=Soft clay detail.png|The golem is nearly whole.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After using the fourth soft clay===
* {{tbox|pic=Soft clay detail.png|You repair the golem with a final piece of clay.}}
* '''Clay golem:''' Damage repaired...
* '''Clay golem:''' Thank you. My body and mind are fully healed.
* '''Clay golem:''' Now I must complete my task by defeating the great enemy.
* '''Player:''' What enemy?
* '''Clay golem:''' A great demon. It broke through from its dimension to attack the city.
* '''Clay golem:''' The golem army was created to fight it. Many were destroyed, but we drove the demon back!
* '''Clay golem:''' The demon is still wounded. You must open the portal so that I can strike the final blow and complete my task.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Golem again after learning about the demon===
* '''Clay golem:''' My task is incomplete. You must open the portal so I can defeat the great demon.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|How do I open the portal?}}
** '''Player:''' How do I open the portal?
** '''Clay golem:''' The four statuettes in the temple must be turned to the correct pattern.
** '''Clay golem:''' I do not know the pattern. Golems are not permitted to open the portal.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What makes you think you can defeat the demon?}}
** '''Player:''' What makes you think you can defeat the demon?
** '''Clay golem:''' If not I, then who else?  No living being can destroy the demon. That is why the golems were created in the first place.
** '''Clay golem:''' But the demon was badly wounded and elder-demons heal very slowly indeed. It was almost dead when it retreated to its own dimension.
** '''Clay golem:''' Now that I am repaired, I will be able to destroy it easily!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'll get right on it.}}
** '''Player:''' I'll get right on it.
** {{tact|end}}

==Visiting the Digsite==
==Talking to Elissa in the Digsite==
* '''Elissa:''' Hello there.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What do you do here?}}
** '''Player:''' What do you do here?
** '''Elissa:''' I'm helping with the dig. I'm an expert on Third Age architecture.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What is this place?}}
** '''Player:''' What is this place?
** '''Elissa:''' In the Third Age, this was a great city. Look at these giant walls! They put Varrock to shame!
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|I don't know, Varrock is pretty impressive.}}
*** '''Player:''' I don't know, Varrock palace is impressive.
*** '''Elissa:''' Hmph. I don't think it will look this good when it's been buried in the ground for three thousand years!
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|What happened to the city?}}
*** '''Player:''' What happened to the city?
*** '''Elissa:''' No one knows for sure.
*** '''Elissa:''' But the Third Age was a time of destruction, when the gods were violently at war.
*** '''Elissa:''' Many great civilizations were destroyed then.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I found a letter in the desert with your name on.}}
** '''Player:''' I found a letter in the desert with your name on.
** '''Elissa:''' Ah, so you've found the ruins of Uzer.
** '''Elissa:''' AI wrote that letter to my late husband when he was exploring there.
** '''Elissa:''' that was a great city as well, but the museum could only fund one excavation and this one was closer to home.
** '''Elissa:''' If you're interested in his expedition, the notes he made are in the library in the Exam Centre.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Elissa again after learning where the notes are===
* '''Elissa:''' Hello there.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What do you do here?}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|What is this place?}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|Where did you say the notes were?}}
** '''Player:''' Where did you say the notes were?
** '''Elissa:''' They're on a bookcase in the Exam Centre.
** {{tact|end}}

===Searching the bookcase===
* {{mes|You search the bookcase}}
* {{tbox|pic=Varmen's notes detail.png|You find Varmen's expedition notes.}}{{^|Drops to floor with full inventory}}
* {{mes|You find Varmen's expedition notes.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Elissa after reading Varmen's notes===
* '''Elissa:''' Hello there.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What do you do here?}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|What is this place?}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|Where is the statuette that Varmen took back from Uzer?}}
** '''Player:''' Where is the statuette that Varmen took back from Uzer?
** '''Elissa:''' The statuette?  Oh, yes...
** '''Elissa:''' That statuette was the only thing we had to show from that expedition.
** '''Elissa:''' It was very worn, but you can still make out a lot of detail. The Uzerians were expert sculptors. It's a pity we only have that small example.
** '''Elissa:''' Now it's on display in the Varrock museum.
** {{tact|end}}

==Visiting the Varrock Museum==
===Talking to Curator Haig in the Varrock Museum===
* '''Curator Haig Halen:''' Welcome to the museum of Varrock.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Fossil Island}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Have you any interesting news?}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Do you know where I could find any treasure?}}
* {{topt|I'm looking for a statuette recovered from the city of Uzer.}}
** '''Player:''' I'm looking for a statuette recovered from the city of Uzer.
** '''Curator Haig Halen:''' Ah yes, a very impressive artefact. The people of that city were excellent sculptors.
** '''Curator Haig Halen:''' It's in the display case upstairs.
** '''Player:''' No, I need to take it away with me.
** '''Curator Haig Halen:''' What do you want it for?
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|I want to open a portal to the lair of an elder-demon.}}
*** '''Player:''' I want to open a portal to the lair of an elder-demon.
*** '''Curator Haig Halen:''' Good heavens! I'd never let you do such a dangerous thing.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Well, I, er, just want it.}}
*** '''Player:''' Well, I, er, just want it.
*** '''Curator Haig Halen:''' Well, you can't have it! This museum never lets go of its treasures.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|How do I get a medallion?}}

===Pickpocketing Curator Haig===
* {{tcond|If the player has not yet learned about the display case:}}
** {{mes|The curator doesn't seem to have anything of value.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tbox|pic=Display cabinet key detail.png|You steal a tiny key.}}{{^|Drops to floor with full inventory}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Opening the display case===
* {{tcond|If the player does not have the key:}}
** {{mes|The cabinet is locked.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player already has the statuette:}}
** {{mes|You have already taken the statuette.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tbox|pic=Statuette (The Golem) detail.png|You open the cabinet and retrieve the statuette.}}{{^|Drops to floor with full inventory}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Curator Haig after losing the statuette===
* '''Curator Haig Halen:''' Welcome to the museum of Varrock.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Fossil Island}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Have you any interesting news?}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Do you know where I could find any treasure?}}
* {{topt|I'm looking for a statuette recovered from the city of Uzer.}}
** '''Player:''' I'm looking for a statuette recovered from the city of Uzer.
** '''Curator Haig Halen:''' Ah yes, a very impressive artefact. The people of that city were excellent sculptors.
** '''Curator Haig Halen:''' It's in the display case upstairs.
** '''Curator Haig Halen:''' That statuette was stolen recently, but now it's been returned.
** '''Player:''' No, I need to take it away with me.
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|quest=No|How do I get a medallion?}}

==Returning to Uzer==
===Using the strange implement on the Golem without the new instructions===
* {{mes|You insert the key and the golem's skull hinges open.}}
* {{mes|The golems skull shuts automatically.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using statuette on alcove===
* {{tcond|If there is already a statuette in the alcove:}}
** {{mes|There is already a statuette in the alcove.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{mes|You insert the statuette into the alcove.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Unlocking the door with statuettes===
* {{mes|The door grinds open.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Trying to turn statuettes after opening the door===
* {{mes|The statuette is now locked in place.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the golem after opening the portal===
* '''Clay golem:''' My task is incomplete. You must open the portal so I can defeat the great demon.
* '''Player:''' I opened the portal.
* '''Clay golem:''' Golems cannot pass through the portal. But the demon will soon emerge. I must ready myself for combat!
* {{tact|end}}

===Entering the portal===
* {{mes|You step into the portal.}}
* {{tcond|If this is the first time the player has entered the portal:}}
** {{mes|This room is dominated by a colossal horned skeleton!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using hammer on throne===
* {{tcond|If the player has no chisel:}}
** {{mes|You'll need a chisel as well as a hammer to get the gems.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the golem after entering the throne of the demon===
* '''Clay golem:''' My task is incomplete. You must open the portal so I can defeat the great demon.
* '''Player:''' It's okay, the demon is dead!
* '''Clay golem:''' The demon must be defeated...
* '''Player:''' No, you don't understand. I saw the demon's skeleton. It must have died of its wounds.
* '''Clay golem:''' Demon must be defeated! Task incomplete.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the golem again after being told the demon must be defeated===
* '''Clay golem:''' My task is incomplete. You must open the portal so I can defeat the great demon.
* '''Player:''' I already told you, he's dead!
* '''Clay golem:''' Task incomplete.
* '''Player:''' Oh, how am I going to convince you?
* {{tact|end}}

===Taking the phoenix feather===
* {{tcond|If the player already has a phoenix feather or quill pen:}}
** {{mes|You already have a phoenix tail-feather.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{mes|You attempt to grab the phoenix's tail-feather.}}
* {{tcond|If the player succeeds:}}
** {{mes|You grab a tail-feather.}}{{^|Drops to ground with full inventory}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player fails:}}
** {{mes|You fail to grab the feather.}}
** '''Desert Phoenix:''' {{overhead|Squawk!}}
** {{mes|You've been stunned!}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Picking a black mushroom===
* {{tbox|You pick a mushroom.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Crushing the mushroom with a pestle and mortar===
* {{tbox|You crush the mushroom and pour the juice into a vial.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Crushing the mushroom without having an empty vial===
* {{tbox|You crush the mushroom, but you have no vial to put the dye in and it goes everywhere!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using the phoenix feather on papyrus===
* {{mes|You will need some kind of ink to write with.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using a phoenix feather on the black dye===
* {{tbox|pic=Phoenix quill pen detail.png|You dip the phoenix feather into the dye.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using the phoenix quill on the papyrus===
* {{tcond|If the player has not learned that the demon is dead:}}
** {{mes|You don't know what to write.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tbox|pic=Golem program detail.png|You write on the papyrus: YOUR TASK IS DONE}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using program on golem before using the strange implement===
* {{mes|You can't see a way to put the instructions in the golem's skull}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After using the strange implement on the golem in Uzer and adding the new instructions===
* '''Clay golem:''' New instructions... Updating program...
* '''Clay golem:''' Task complete!
* '''Clay golem:''' Thank you. Now my mind is at rest.
* {{tact|end}}

==Post quest==
===Talking to the Golem===
* '''Clay golem:''' Thank you for helping me. A golem can have no greater satisfaction than knowing that its task is complete.
* '''Player:''' But the whole city is destroyed! Doesn't that bother you?
* '''Clay golem:''' I was never programmed to appreciate the city. My only purpose was the destruction of the demon, and that is achieved!
* {{tact|end}}

{{The Golem}}
